<br>
Having farmed acrylia myself, I would argue with the assertion that 30-40pp is &quot;1/3 of what they're worth&quot;.  Especially since most of the acrylia being sold is just stuff that happened to drop while people were hunting in MT, grimling, etc. Those who farm acrylia are generally doing it for their own sake, not to sell it. I can think of much more profitable ways to spend your time, even if acrylia prices were double what they are now. I'm not ignorant of how capitalism works. You can sell it for whatever you want to. Nobody can twist my arm and make me buy acrylia for any more than I want to pay. I'm not calling for the death of any acrylia vendors. At the same time, supply and demand dictates that acrylia is <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>worth</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> whatever people are willing to pay for it, which in turn is driven by however much they can get for the items they make from it. If you sell it so high that people lose money, they won't buy. I keep thinking that the prices will eventually adjust to something more reasonable, but this has been going on for about a month now. Who's buying it at these prices?<br>
<br>
P.S.<br>
